ciscoPopMgmtMIB.name: ciscoPopMgmtMIB

revisions.description: Imported dsx1LineIndex from DS1-MIB instead of RFC1406-MIB Changed SYNTAX of cpmDS1SlotIndex cpmDS1PortIndex cpmChannelIndex cpmDS1UsageSlotIndex cpmDS1UsagePortIndex cpmActiveCallSummaryIndex cpmCallHistorySummaryIndex cpmActiveModemSlot cpmActiveModemPort cpmActiveEntrySlot cpmActiveEntryPort cpmActiveEntryChannel from Integer32 to Integer32 (0..2147483647) Imported Unsigned32 from SNMPv2-SMI instead of CISCO-TC.
Added voice(6) to object cpmCallType. Added Notification Group cpmNotificationGroupRev1
Added cpmCallVolume with objects: cpmCallVolSuccISDNDigital cpmCallVolAnalogCallClearedNormally

Extended cpmDs1DS0UsageTable with objects: cpmDS1TotalAnalogCalls cpmDS1TotalDigitalCalls cpmDS1TotalV110Calls cpmDS1TotalV120Calls cpmDS1TotalCalls cpmDS1TotalTimeInUse cpmDS1CurrentIdle cpmDS1CurrentOutOfService cpmDS1CurrentBusyout cpmDS1InOctets cpmDS1OutOctets cpmDS1InPackets cpmDS1OutPackets Added system level summary objects: cpmISDNCfgActiveDChannels cpmISDNCfgBChannelsTimeInUse cpmISDNCfgBChannelsTimeInUseAnalog cpmISDNCfgBChannelCalls cpmISDNCfgBChannelAnalogCalls cpmTotalISDNSyncPPPCalls Added DS0StatusTable with objects: cpmDS0OperStatus cpmDS0BusyoutAdminStatus cpmDS0BusyoutAllow cpmDS0BusyoutStatus cpmDS0BusyoutSource cpmDS0BusyoutTime cpmDS0ConfigFunction cpmDS0InterfaceIndex Added busyout notification and notification enable object: cpmDS0BusyoutNotification cpmDS0BusyoutNotifyEnable cpmDS1LoopbackNotifyConfig cpmDS1LoopbackNotifyEnable cpmDS1LoopbackNotification
Added objects: cpmISDNCfgBChanInUseForVoice cpmCASCfgBChanInUseForVoice Added enumeration-type: voice
Initial version of this MIB module.

ciscoPopMgmtMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-apm@cisco.com
ciscoPopMgmtMIB.description: Cisco Point Of Presence Management MIB to provide DSX1 and DSX0 facilities management and call summaries.

cpmDS0UsageTable.name: cpmDS0UsageTable
cpmDS0UsageTable.description: The DS0 usage table is for hardware and software objects not used as interfaces, and not covered in rfc1213. These objects include analog calls coming over ISDN, Channelized T1, and Channelized E1. This table is created for every DS1 line in the device.

cpmDS0UsageEntry.name: cpmDS0UsageEntry
cpmDS0UsageEntry.description: An entry in the DS0 Usage table.

cpmDS1SlotIndex.name: cpmDS1SlotIndex
cpmDS1SlotIndex.description: The slot index indicates the slot number on the device where the DS1 card resides.

cpmDS1PortIndex.name: cpmDS1PortIndex
cpmDS1PortIndex.description: The port index indicates the port number of a specific DS1 on the DS1 card in the slot

cpmChannelIndex.name: cpmChannelIndex
cpmChannelIndex.description: The channel index that distinguishes the DS0 timeslot of the DS1 port. The range of the channel index is based on the number of T1/E1 channels: 1-24(T1) and 1-31(E1).

cpmConfiguredType.name: cpmConfiguredType
cpmConfiguredType.description: The configured technology for the channel: ISDN(2), Channelized T1 (3) or Channelized E1 (4).

cpmDS0CallType.name: cpmDS0CallType
cpmDS0CallType.description: The type of the current call carried by this DS0. idle - This DS0 is currently idle. unknown - The data type of the call currently occupying this DS0 is not one of the types listed here. analog - The data type of the call currently occupying this DS0 is analog, i.e. a modem call. digital - The data type of the call currently occupying this DS0 is digital. v110 - The call currently occupying this DS0 is a V110 call. v120 - The call currently occupying this DS0 is a V120 call. voice - The call currently occupying this DS0 is a voice call.

cpmL2Encapsulation.name: cpmL2Encapsulation
cpmL2Encapsulation.description: The data link encapsulation of the call currently occuppying this DS0: idle - This DS0 is currently idle. unknown - The encapsulation of the currently active call on this DS0 is not one of the options following. PPP - slip - arap - hdlc - exec - voice - voice encapsulation; IANA type voiceEncap(103)

cpmCallCount.name: cpmCallCount
cpmCallCount.description: The number of calls that have occupied this DS0.

cpmTimeInUse.name: cpmTimeInUse
cpmTimeInUse.description: The amount of time that this DS0 has been in use. This is computed by summing up the call durations of all past calls that have occupied this DS0.

cpmInOctets.name: cpmInOctets
cpmInOctets.description: The total number of octets received on this DS0 for data calls (cpmDS0CallType has the value 'analog(3)' or 'digital(4)' or 'v110(5)' or 'v120(6)'). All the received 'raw' octets are counted, including any protocol headers which may or may not be present, depending on the service type of data call.

cpmOutOctets.name: cpmOutOctets
cpmOutOctets.description: The total number of octets transmitted on this DS0 for data calls (cpmDS0CallType has the value 'analog(3)' or 'digital(4)' or 'v110(5)' or 'v120(6)'). All the transmitted 'raw' octets are counted, including any protocol headers which may or may not be present, depending on the service type of data call.

cpmInPackets.name: cpmInPackets
cpmInPackets.description: The total number of packets received on this DS0 for data calls (cpmDS0CallTyp has the value 'analog(3)' or 'digital(4)' or 'v110(5)' or 'v120(6)').

cpmOutPackets.name: cpmOutPackets
cpmOutPackets.description: The total number of packets transmitted on this DS0 for data calls (cpmDS0CallTyp has the value 'analog(3)' or 'digital(4)' or 'v110(5)' or 'v120(6)').

cpmAssociatedInterface.name: cpmAssociatedInterface
cpmAssociatedInterface.description: This is the value of ifIndex when the specific channel has an active call with a corresponding interface in the ifTable. For example, a digital ISDN call has a value pointing to the B-Channel entry in the ifTable. A modem call over ISDN or CT1/CE1 has a value pointing to the async interface of the modem assigned to this call. If the channel is idle, this value is 0.

cpmISDNCfgBChanInUseForAnalog.name: cpmISDNCfgBChanInUseForAnalog
cpmISDNCfgBChanInUseForAnalog.description: The number of configured ISDN B-Channels that are currently occupied by analog calls.

cpmISDNCfgBChannelsInUse.name: cpmISDNCfgBChannelsInUse
cpmISDNCfgBChannelsInUse.description: The number of configured ISDN B-Channels that are currently occupied by both Digital and Analog calls.

cpmActiveDS0s.name: cpmActiveDS0s
cpmActiveDS0s.description: The number of DS0s that are currently in use.

cpmPPPCalls.name: cpmPPPCalls
cpmPPPCalls.description: The current number of active PPP calls received by the managed device

cpmV120Calls.name: cpmV120Calls
cpmV120Calls.description: The current number of active V.120 calls received by the managed device

cpmV110Calls.name: cpmV110Calls
cpmV110Calls.description: The current number of active V.110 calls received by the managed device

cpmActiveDS0sHighWaterMark.name: cpmActiveDS0sHighWaterMark
cpmActiveDS0sHighWaterMark.description: The high water mark for number of DS0s that are active simultaneously

cpmDS1DS0UsageTable.name: cpmDS1DS0UsageTable
cpmDS1DS0UsageTable.description: The DS1-DS0-usage table is for hardware and software objects not used as interfaces, and not covered in rfc1213. These objects provide information on timeslots usage for a particular DS1.

cpmDS1DS0UsageEntry.name: cpmDS1DS0UsageEntry
cpmDS1DS0UsageEntry.description: An entry in the DS0 Usage table.

cpmDS1UsageSlotIndex.name: cpmDS1UsageSlotIndex
cpmDS1UsageSlotIndex.description: The slot index indicates the slot number on the device where the DS1 card resides. The slot index of the first slot is starting from 0 and increment by 1 for the next slot in the device.

cpmDS1UsagePortIndex.name: cpmDS1UsagePortIndex
cpmDS1UsagePortIndex.description: The port index indicates the port number of a specific DS1 on the DS1 card in the slot. The port index of the first port is starting from 0 and increment by 1 for the next port on the DS1 card.

cpmDS1ActiveDS0s.name: cpmDS1ActiveDS0s
cpmDS1ActiveDS0s.description: The number of DS0s that are currently in use for a particular DS1.

cpmDS1ActiveDS0sHighWaterMark.name: cpmDS1ActiveDS0sHighWaterMark
cpmDS1ActiveDS0sHighWaterMark.description: The highest number of simultaneously actived DS0s on a specified DS1.

cpmDS1TotalAnalogCalls.name: cpmDS1TotalAnalogCalls
cpmDS1TotalAnalogCalls.description: The accumulated number of analog data calls (cpmDS0CallType has the value 'analog(3)') on all ds0s within this DS1 since system startup. The object includes active and terminated calls.

cpmDS1TotalDigitalCalls.name: cpmDS1TotalDigitalCalls
cpmDS1TotalDigitalCalls.description: The accumulated number of digital data calls (cpmDS0CallType has the value 'digital(4)') on all ds0s within this DS1 since system startup. The object includes active and terminated calls.

cpmDS1TotalV110Calls.name: cpmDS1TotalV110Calls
cpmDS1TotalV110Calls.description: The accumulated number of v.110 data calls (cpmDS0CallType has the value 'v110(5)') on all ds0s within this DS1 since system startup. The object includes active and terminated calls.

cpmDS1TotalV120Calls.name: cpmDS1TotalV120Calls
cpmDS1TotalV120Calls.description: The accumulated number of v.120 data calls (cpmDS0CallType has the value 'v120(6)') on all ds0s within this DS1 since system startup. The object includes active and terminated calls.

cpmDS1TotalCalls.name: cpmDS1TotalCalls
cpmDS1TotalCalls.description: The total number of calls on all the DS0s within this DS1 since last system re-initialization. The object includes active and terminated calls. This only includes DS0s configured as bearer channels, not those configured for signaling, such as PRI D-channel.

cpmDS1TotalTimeInUse.name: cpmDS1TotalTimeInUse
cpmDS1TotalTimeInUse.description: The total call duration on all the DS0s within this DS1 since last system re-initialization. This only includes DS0s configured as bearer channels, not those configured for signaling, such as PRI D-channel.

cpmDS1CurrentIdle.name: cpmDS1CurrentIdle
cpmDS1CurrentIdle.description: The total number of DS0s currently in idle state within this DS1. This only includes DS0s configured as bearer and CAS channels, not those configured for signaling, such as PRI D-channel. See cpmDS0OperStatus in the cpmDS0StatusTable for individual DS0s.

cpmDS1CurrentOutOfService.name: cpmDS1CurrentOutOfService
cpmDS1CurrentOutOfService.description: The total number of DS0s in this DS1 currently placed out of service. This only includes DS0s configured as bearer and CAS channels, not those configured for signaling, such as PRI D-channel. See cpmDS0OperStatus in the cpmDS0StatusTable for individual DS0s.

cpmDS1CurrentBusyout.name: cpmDS1CurrentBusyout
cpmDS1CurrentBusyout.description: The total number of DS0s in this DS1 which currently have been requested to be busied out, but are not yet out of service. When an active call on a busied out DS0 terminates, the DS0 will be out of service, this object will be decremented and cpmDS1TotalOutOfService will be incremented. This only includes DS0s configured as bearer channels, not those configured for signaling, such as PRI D-channel. See cpmDS0AdminStatus in the cpmDS0StatusTable for individual DS0s.

cpmDS1InOctets.name: cpmDS1InOctets
cpmDS1InOctets.description: The total number of octets received over all the DS0 bearer channels within this DS1 since last system re-initialization. This value is a sum of all the cpmInOctets objects in the cpmDS0UsageTable for this DS1.

cpmDS1OutOctets.name: cpmDS1OutOctets
cpmDS1OutOctets.description: The total number of octets transmitted over all the DS0 bearer channels within this DS1 since last system re-initialization. This value is a sum of all the cpmOutOctets objects in the cpmDS0UsageTable for this DS1.

cpmDS1InPackets.name: cpmDS1InPackets
cpmDS1InPackets.description: The total number of data packets received over all the DS0 bearer channels within this DS1 since last system re-initialization. This value is a sum of all the cpmInPackets objects in the cpmDS0UsageTable for this DS1. It consists of PPP or PCM voice data packets.

cpmDS1OutPackets.name: cpmDS1OutPackets
cpmDS1OutPackets.description: The total number of data packets transmitted over all the DS0 bearer channels within this DS1 since last system re-initialization. This value is a sum of all the cpmOutPackets objects in the cpmDS0UsageTable for this DS1. It consists of PPP or PCM voice data packets.

cpmSW56CfgBChannelsInUse.name: cpmSW56CfgBChannelsInUse
cpmSW56CfgBChannelsInUse.description: The number of configured SW56 B-Channels that are currently occupied by Digital calls.

cpmISDNCfgBChanInUseForVoice.name: cpmISDNCfgBChanInUseForVoice
cpmISDNCfgBChanInUseForVoice.description: The number of configured ISDN B-Channels that are currently occupied by Voice calls.

cpmCASCfgBChanInUseForVoice.name: cpmCASCfgBChanInUseForVoice
cpmCASCfgBChanInUseForVoice.description: The number of configured CAS Channels that are currently occupied by Voice calls.

cpmISDNCfgActiveDChannels.name: cpmISDNCfgActiveDChannels
cpmISDNCfgActiveDChannels.description: The number of ISDN signaling channels which are active.

cpmISDNCfgBChannelsTimeInUse.name: cpmISDNCfgBChannelsTimeInUse
cpmISDNCfgBChannelsTimeInUse.description: The total call duration on all the ISDN B-channels since last system re-initialization.

cpmISDNCfgBChannelsTimeInUseAnlg.name: cpmISDNCfgBChannelsTimeInUseAnlg
cpmISDNCfgBChannelsTimeInUseAnlg.description: The total analog call duration on all the ISDN B-channels since last system re-initialization. Analog call type is identified in cpmDS0CallType.

cpmISDNCfgBChannelCalls.name: cpmISDNCfgBChannelCalls
cpmISDNCfgBChannelCalls.description: The total number of calls on all the ISDN B-channels since last system re-initialization.

cpmISDNCfgBChannelAnalogCalls.name: cpmISDNCfgBChannelAnalogCalls
cpmISDNCfgBChannelAnalogCalls.description: The total number of analog calls on all the ISDN B-channels since last system re-initialization. Analog call type is identified in cpmDS0CallType.

cpmTotalISDNSyncPPPCalls.name: cpmTotalISDNSyncPPPCalls
cpmTotalISDNSyncPPPCalls.description: The total number of ISDN-sync PPP calls received by the managed device since last system re-initialization.

cpmDS0BusyoutNotifyEnable.name: cpmDS0BusyoutNotifyEnable
cpmDS0BusyoutNotifyEnable.description: This variable controls generation of cpmDS0BusyoutNotification. When this variable is 'true(1)', generation of cpmDS0BusyoutNotification is enabled. When this variable is 'false(2)', generation of cpmDS0BusyoutNotification is disabled. The default value is 'false(2)'.

cpmDS0StatusTable.name: cpmDS0StatusTable
cpmDS0StatusTable.description: The DS0 Status Table provides additional DS0 level information and configuration. This table is an extension of the cpmDS0UsageTable.

cpmDS0StatusEntry.name: cpmDS0StatusEntry
cpmDS0StatusEntry.description: Status for an individual DS0. This entry AUGMENTS the cpmDS0UsageEntry. An entry exists for each configured DS0 in the system.

cpmDS0OperStatus.name: cpmDS0OperStatus
cpmDS0OperStatus.description: The operational state of the DSO. This object provides more detailed information than the IF-MIB ifOperStatus. unknown - The DSO is in an unknown state down - The DS0 is out of service idle - This DS0 is currently idle setup - A new connection is in the process of being established connected - A active connection exists test - The DSO is undergoing internal testing

cpmDS0BusyoutAdminStatus.name: cpmDS0BusyoutAdminStatus
cpmDS0BusyoutAdminStatus.description: The administratively requested busyout state of the DSO. This object represents the desired busyout state of the DS0, which may or may not be reflected in the operation state, cpmDS0OperStatus. This object may be set via SNMP or the system console. noBusyout - No administrative busyout has been requested busyout - The DS0 will be shutdown when it next transitions to idle(2) cpmDS0OperStatus busyoutImmediate - Immediately transition the DS0 to down(2), terminating any current activity The effect of setting this object to busyout or busyoutImmediate is constrained by the value of cpmDS0BusyoutAllowed. If cpmDS0BusyoutAllowed has a value of false, attempting to set this object to busyout or busyoutImmediate will fail. This object provides more busyout information not available from the IF-MIB ifAdminStatus. This object reflects busyout requests configured on the local system as defined for the object cpmDS0BusyoutSource.

cpmDS0BusyoutAllow.name: cpmDS0BusyoutAllow
cpmDS0BusyoutAllow.description: The object indicates if busyout requests for this DSO will be allowed. true - Setting cpmDS0BusyoutAdminStatus to busyout(2) or busyoutImmediate(3) will be accepted false - Busyout requests for this DS0 are not allowed The default value is true(1). If cpmDS0BusyoutAllowed has a value of false(2), attempting to set cpmDS0BusyoutAdminStatus to busyout or busyoutImmediate will fail. This object only constrains setting the value of cpmDS0BusyoutAdminStatus when cpmDS0BusyoutAdminStatus is set via SNMP.

cpmDS0BusyoutStatus.name: cpmDS0BusyoutStatus
cpmDS0BusyoutStatus.description: The busyout status of the DSO. noBusyout - The DS0 is not busied out nor has a busyout pending. busyoutPending - The DS0 has a busyout request pending. It will shutdown when it next transitions to idle(2) cpmDS0OperStatus. busiedOut - The DS0 is out of service due to a busyout request. This object is needed to reflect busyouts initiated other than administrativly, as described in cpmDS0BusyoutSource.

cpmDS0BusyoutSource.name: cpmDS0BusyoutSource
cpmDS0BusyoutSource.description: The source of the busyout request either pending or active for the DSO. none - The DS0 is not busied out nor has a busyout request pending local - The DS0 is busied out or has a pending request due to an adminstrative command issued locally. internal - The DS0 is busied out or has a pending request due to internal system processing. remote - The DS0 is busied out or has a pending request due to a request from the peer switch.

cpmDS0BusyoutTime.name: cpmDS0BusyoutTime
cpmDS0BusyoutTime.description: Value of sysUpTime when the most recent busyout request was issued for this DS0. The value is zero indicates no busyout request has been issued.

cpmDS0ConfigFunction.name: cpmDS0ConfigFunction
cpmDS0ConfigFunction.description: The object indicates the function this DSO is configured to provide. This object provides more detail than cpmConfiguredType. unknown - Unknown configuration t1SignallingChan - DS0 is configured as a T1 common channel signalling (CCS) such as ISDN PRI D-channel t1CcsBearerChan - DS0 is configured as a T1 common channel signalling (CCS) bearer channel e1SignallingChan - DS0 is configured as a E1 common channel signalling (CCS) such as ISDN PRI D-channel e1CcsBearerChan - DS0 is configured as a E1 common channel signalling (CCS) bearer channel t1CasChan - DS0 is configured as a T1 channel associated signalling channel e1CasChan - DS0 is configured as a E1 channel associated signalling channel

cpmDS0InterfaceIndex.name: cpmDS0InterfaceIndex
cpmDS0InterfaceIndex.description: This is the value of ifIndex in the ifTable for this DS0.

cpmISDNCallsRejected.name: cpmISDNCallsRejected
cpmISDNCallsRejected.description: The number of rejected ISDN calls in this managed device.

cpmModemCallsRejected.name: cpmModemCallsRejected
cpmModemCallsRejected.description: The number of rejected modem calls in this managed device.

cpmISDNCallsClearedAbnormally.name: cpmISDNCallsClearedAbnormally
cpmISDNCallsClearedAbnormally.description: The number of connected ISDN calls that have been abnormally cleared, that is, they were cleared by some event other than the following: a - The transmission of a normal disconnect message by the local end. b - The reception of a normal disconnect message from the remote end.

cpmModemCallsClearedAbnormally.name: cpmModemCallsClearedAbnormally
cpmModemCallsClearedAbnormally.description: The number of connected modem calls that have been abnormally cleared, that is, they were not cleared with the proper modem protocol handshakes.

cpmISDNNoResource.name: cpmISDNNoResource
cpmISDNNoResource.description: The number of ISDN calls that have been rejected because there is no B-Channel available to handle the call.

cpmModemNoResource.name: cpmModemNoResource
cpmModemNoResource.description: The number of modem calls that have been rejected because there is no modem available to handle the call.

cpmCallVolSuccISDNDigital.name: cpmCallVolSuccISDNDigital
cpmCallVolSuccISDNDigital.description: The number of incoming and outgoing successful ISDN digital data calls (cpmDS0CallType has the value 'digital(4)'), since system startup. A successful call is a terminated call that has a disconnect cause of 'normal call clearing(16)'.

cpmCallVolAnalogCallClearedNormally.name: cpmCallVolAnalogCallClearedNormally
cpmCallVolAnalogCallClearedNormally.description: The number of incoming and outgoing successful analog data calls which use modem resource (cpmDS0CallType has the value 'analog(3)'), since system startup. A successful call is a terminated call who is cleared by the proper modem protocol handshake.

cpmActiveCallSummaryTable.name: cpmActiveCallSummaryTable
cpmActiveCallSummaryTable.description: The active call summary table is needed to track currently active calls. This table is needed because modem calls are not in CALL-HISTORY-MIB, and the DIAL-CONTROL_MIB is not yet available.

cpmActiveCallSummaryEntry.name: cpmActiveCallSummaryEntry
cpmActiveCallSummaryEntry.description: An entry in the Call Summary table.

cpmActiveCallStartTimeIndex.name: cpmActiveCallStartTimeIndex
cpmActiveCallStartTimeIndex.description: The start time of the current call.

cpmActiveCallSummaryIndex.name: cpmActiveCallSummaryIndex
cpmActiveCallSummaryIndex.description: Arbitrary small integer to distinguish calls that occured at the same time tick.

cpmActiveUserID.name: cpmActiveUserID
cpmActiveUserID.description: The User login ID or zero length string if unavailable.

cpmActiveUserIpAddr.name: cpmActiveUserIpAddr
cpmActiveUserIpAddr.description: The IP address of the call or 0.0.0.0 if unavailable. This object comes directly from IOS.

cpmActiveCallType.name: cpmActiveCallType
cpmActiveCallType.description: The call type: unknown - None of the following analog - Modem call digital - Digital call v110 - V110 Call v120 - V120 Call voice - Voice Call

cpmActiveModemSlot.name: cpmActiveModemSlot
cpmActiveModemSlot.description: Identification of modem resource allocated to call. This is the value of cmSlotIndex from CISCO-MODEM-MGMT-MIB. This value along with cpmActiveModemPort uniquely identifies a modem. Value is -1 if call does not utilize a modem.

cpmActiveModemPort.name: cpmActiveModemPort
cpmActiveModemPort.description: Identification of modem resource allocated to call. This is the value of cmPortIndex from CISCO-MODEM-MGMT-MIB. This value along with cpmActiveModemSlot uniquely identifies a modem. Value is -1 if call does not utilize a modem.

cpmActiveCallDuration.name: cpmActiveCallDuration
cpmActiveCallDuration.description: The duration of the current call.

cpmActiveEntrySlot.name: cpmActiveEntrySlot
cpmActiveEntrySlot.description: The logical slot in which the DS1 line that the user connected on resides.

cpmActiveEntryPort.name: cpmActiveEntryPort
cpmActiveEntryPort.description: The logical port for the DS1 line that the user connected on.

cpmActiveEntryChannel.name: cpmActiveEntryChannel
cpmActiveEntryChannel.description: The channel within the DS1 that is allocated to the call.

cpmActiveRemotePhoneNumber.name: cpmActiveRemotePhoneNumber
cpmActiveRemotePhoneNumber.description: The remote telephone number. For a call into the device, this is the originating number. For a call out of the device, this is the dialed number. If not available the string length is zero.

cpmActiveLocalPhoneNumber.name: cpmActiveLocalPhoneNumber
cpmActiveLocalPhoneNumber.description: The local telephone number. For a call into the device, this is the dialed number. For a call out of the device, this is the originating number. If not available the string length is zero.

cpmActiveTTYNumber.name: cpmActiveTTYNumber
cpmActiveTTYNumber.description: The TTY number associated with this call. This information comes from the IOS 'show line' command.

cpmCallHistorySummaryTableMaxLength.name: cpmCallHistorySummaryTableMaxLength
cpmCallHistorySummaryTableMaxLength.description: The upper limit on the number of entries that the cpmCallHistoryTable may contain. A value of 0 will prevent any history from being retained. When this table is full, the oldest entry will be deleted and the new one will be created.

cpmCallHistorySummaryRetainTimer.name: cpmCallHistorySummaryRetainTimer
cpmCallHistorySummaryRetainTimer.description: The minimum amount of time that an cpmCallHistoryEntry will be maintained before being deleted. A value of 0 will prevent any history from being retained, but will not prevent callCompletion traps being genarated.

cpmCallHistorySummaryTable.name: cpmCallHistorySummaryTable
cpmCallHistorySummaryTable.description: The call history summary table is needed to track ended active calls. This table is needed because modem calls are not in CALL-HISTORY-MIB; the CISCO-ISDN-MIB objects do not contain information about the active calls; and the DIAL-CONTROL_MIB is not yet available.

cpmCallHistorySummaryEntry.name: cpmCallHistorySummaryEntry
cpmCallHistorySummaryEntry.description: An entry in the Call Summary table.

cpmCallDisconnectTimeIndex.name: cpmCallDisconnectTimeIndex
cpmCallDisconnectTimeIndex.description: The disconnect time of the call.

cpmCallStartTimeIndex.name: cpmCallStartTimeIndex
cpmCallStartTimeIndex.description: The start time of the current call.

cpmCallHistorySummaryIndex.name: cpmCallHistorySummaryIndex
cpmCallHistorySummaryIndex.description: Arbitrary small integer to distinguish calls that occured at the same time tick.

cpmUserID.name: cpmUserID
cpmUserID.description: The User login ID or zero length string if unavailable. This object comes directly from IOS.

cpmUserIpAddr.name: cpmUserIpAddr
cpmUserIpAddr.description: The IP address of the call or 0.0.0.0 if unavailable. This object comes directly from IOS.

cpmCallType.name: cpmCallType
cpmCallType.description: The call type: unknown - None of the following analog - Modem call digital - Digital call v110 - V110 Call v120 - V120 Call voice - Voice Call

cpmModemSlot.name: cpmModemSlot
cpmModemSlot.description: Identification of modem resource allocated to call. This is the value of cmSlotIndex from CISCO-MODEM-MGMT-MIB. This value along with cpmModemPort uniquely identifies a modem. Value is -1 if call does not utilize a modem.

cpmModemPort.name: cpmModemPort
cpmModemPort.description: Identification of modem resource allocated to call. This is the value of cmPortIndex from CISCO-MODEM-MGMT-MIB. This value along with cpmModemSlot uniquely identifies a modem. Value is -1 if call does not utilize a modem.

cpmCallDuration.name: cpmCallDuration
cpmCallDuration.description: The duration of the current call.

cpmEntrySlot.name: cpmEntrySlot
cpmEntrySlot.description: The physical system slot in which the DS1 line that the user connected on resides.

cpmEntryPort.name: cpmEntryPort
cpmEntryPort.description: The logical port for the DS1 line that the user connected on.

cpmEntryChannel.name: cpmEntryChannel
cpmEntryChannel.description: The channel within the DS1 that is allocated to the call.

cpmRemotePhoneNumber.name: cpmRemotePhoneNumber
cpmRemotePhoneNumber.description: The remote telephone number. For a call into the device, this is the originating number. For a call out of the device, this is the dialed number. If not available the string length is zero.

cpmLocalPhoneNumber.name: cpmLocalPhoneNumber
cpmLocalPhoneNumber.description: The local telephone number. For a call into the device, this is the dialed number. For a call out of the device, this is the originating number. If not available the string length is zero.

cpmTTYNumber.name: cpmTTYNumber
